Define the default 'boring' templates that iterate over signature metadata. These make prompt templates simple and type-driven.

Location: crates/dspy-rs/src/signature/compiled.rs

```rust
/// Default system template - describes input/output fields
pub const DEFAULT_SYSTEM_TEMPLATE: &str = r#"
Your input fields are:
{% for f in sig.inputs -%}
- {{ f.llm_name }}: {{ f.type_name }}
{% endfor %}

Your output fields are:
{% for f in sig.outputs -%}
- {{ f.llm_name }}: {{ f.type_name }}
{% if f.schema %}
{{ f.schema }}
{% endif %}
{% endfor %}
"#;

/// Default user template - renders actual input values
pub const DEFAULT_USER_TEMPLATE: &str = r#"
{% for f in sig.inputs %}
[[ ## {{ f.llm_name }} ## ]]
{{ inputs[f.rust_name] }}

{% endfor %}
"#;
```

These templates:
- Use sig.inputs/sig.outputs for metadata iteration
- Access actual values via inputs[f.rust_name]
- The {{ inputs[f.rust_name] }} triggers JinjaPromptValue rendering
- Schema is included for output fields (helps model understand expected format)

Register these in PromptWorld construction:
```rust
world.jinja.add_template_owned('sig::system', DEFAULT_SYSTEM_TEMPLATE.to_string())?;
world.jinja.add_template_owned('sig::user', DEFAULT_USER_TEMPLATE.to_string())?;
```
